cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Risk-Aware Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning for Cloudburst Disaster Response"
abstract: >
  A constrained multi-agent reinforcement learning framework (LagrangianCTDE)
  that coordinates Storm, Flood, and Evacuation response agents under formal
  safety constraints. Combines a two-stream ViT perception module fusing NEXRAD
  radar and GOES-16 satellite imagery with a Lagrangian primal-dual PPO
  training algorithm (CTDE). Achieves 81.5 ± 2.6 cumulative reward at 2.3%
  safety violation rate, outperforming six baselines including MAPPO and CPO.
